            Welcome Back Networking Social at Electric Garden
          Heading link



 
Copy link








Each semester, UIC Business hosts networking socials for graduate students to connect with their peers and staff. This group gathered at campus neighbor, Electric Garden.









            Graduate Student Organizations
          Heading link



 
Copy link



UIC Business’ many student organizations complement our academic programs with hands-on leadership and networking opportunities with faculty members, alumni and the business community. These organizations, all developed and led by students, reflect our students’ interest in enriching the academic, social and community involvement that is part of our UIC graduate experience. With many student organizations and events, as well as cultural activities and professional opportunities offered in the city of Chicago, UIC Business Liautaud Graduate School students are never without an opportunity to enhance their graduate business school experience.





            UIC Liautaud Student Organizations
          Heading link



 
Copy link












                            Accounting Club
                    

                A professional and social club for students interested in the field of accounting.
            












                            Alpha Kappa Psi
                    

                The premier developer of principled business leaders.
            












                            Association of Latino Professionals For America
                    

                A professional and social club for undergraduate and graduate students that support Latinx students in business.
            












                            Beta Gamma Sigma
                    

                Wishes to encourage and reward scholarship and accomplishment among students.
            












                            Black Students in Business
                    

                Addresses the interests and needs of Black students at UIC Business.
            












                            Business Analytics Organization
                    

                Promotes the intellectual and professional development of students with an interest in business analytics.
            












                            FCG Consulting
                    

                Equipping members with the necessary resources and skills to be prepared for the business and consulting world.
            












                            Finance and Investment Group
                    

                Dedicated to helping finance students with career opportunities in the world of finance.
            












                            Improv Club
                    

                Practicing and participating in improv games to grow valuable relationship skills used in business.
            












                            Informs
                    

                Institute for Operations Research and the Management Systems serves the scientific and professional needs.
            












                            Management Leadership Association
                    












                            Operations Management Group
                    

                Aims to enhance operations and supply chain education and networking opportunities for students.
            












                            Portfolio Management Team
                    

                A student-run investment club that actively manages a paper portfolio in an effort to outperform certain benchmarks.
            












                            United Women’s Network
                    

                Fostering an empowering community of women pursuing their graduate studies at UIC.
            












